title: Jake Paul vs. Gervonta Davis – Props
description: This is a polymarket on predicting the boxing bout between Jake Paul and Gervonta Davis.

markets.question: Will there be an on-stage brawl during the official weigh-in?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if Jake Paul and Gervonta Davis engage in unauthorized physical contact (such as pushing, striking, or grappling) during or immediately after the official weigh-in event. Otherwise, it will resolve to “No.”

Mere face-offs, pointing, verbal exchanges, or security intervention without physical contact will not qualify.

If the bout does not occur for any reason or is postponed beyond December 31, 2025, the market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be the official broadcast or livestream of the weigh-in event. A consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

markets.question: Will either fighter be knocked down in Round 1?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if either Jake Paul or Gervonta Davis is knocked down at any point during Round 1 of their bout. Otherwise, it will resolve to “No.”

For this market, a fighter will be considered “knocked down” if they are struck by a legal blow such that (1) any part of their body other than the feet touches the canvas, or (2) they are held up by or hanging on the ropes (i.e., would have fallen without the ropes), in either case resulting in the referee delivering a mandatory count or stopping the fight due to a knockout.

Accidental slips, trips, or falls will not count as knockdowns.

If the bout does not occur for any reason or is postponed beyond December 31, 2025, the market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be the official broadcast of the bout on Netflix. A consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

markets.question: Will Jake Paul land more punches than Gervonta Davis?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if Jake Paul lands more total punches than Gervonta Davis, according to the official post-fight punch statistics. Otherwise, it will resolve to “No.”

For this market, “total punches” refers to the officially recorded number of landed punches, including both jabs and power punches, as published by the bout’s recognized statistical provider.

If no official punch statistics are released, the bout does not occur for any reason, or it is postponed beyond December 31, 2025, the market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be the official punch statistics released for the bout. However, the official broadcast of the bout on Netflix and a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

markets.question: Will a fighter win by knockout?
markets.description:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if either Jake Paul or Gervonta Davis wins the bout by knockout (KO) or technical knockout (TKO). Otherwise, it will resolve to “No.”

For this market, a knockout (KO) occurs when a fighter is unable to rise and continue fighting after being knocked down within the referee’s count. A technical knockout (TKO) occurs when the referee, ringside doctor, or a fighter’s corner stops the fight because the fighter cannot safely continue.

If the bout does not occur for any reason or is postponed beyond December 31, 2025, the market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be the official broadcast of the bout on Netflix. A consensus of credible reporting may also be used.
